definition: to fish out/to take out (from a pocket, bag etc)

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)

sentences.english: Grab your tissues and find out in this touching weeper.

sentences.english: That pile of earth came from the hole we dug in the ground.

sentences.chinese: 杰弗里伸向他的法衣内并掏出两把手枪。

sentences.english: He pulled off his gloves, took out his matches, and lighted the fire.
sentences.chinese: 他脱下了自己的手套，掏出了火柴，点燃了火苗。

sentences.chinese: 她从口袋里掏出一束传单。

sentences.english: As he stepped up to the cab, he pulled a gole watch from his pocket.

sentences.chinese: 他耸耸肩，只得从口袋里面掏出一只笔来。
